The paper discusses the use of integer programming algorithms in parameterized complexity, which involves analyzing the complexity of algorithms with respect to a parameter. This suggests that the paper may belong to the categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), or cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The specific case studies mentioned in the abstract (Capacitated Dominating Set, Sum Coloring, and Max-q-Cut) also suggest a focus on graph theory and combinatorial optimization, which further supports the likelihood of these categories.
